Yes, I can write a few classes without providing the implementation details. For example, the following classes can be written:

class Segment:
    def __init__(self, start, end):
        self.start = start
        self.end = end

class Triangle:
    def __init__(self, a, b, c):
        self.a = a
        self.b = b
        self.c = c

class Quadrilateral:
    def __init__(self, a, b, c, d):
        self.a = a
        self.b = b
        self.c = c
        self.d = d

class Tetrahedron:
    def __init__(self, a, b, c, d):
        self.a = a
        self.b = b
        self.c = c
        self.d = d
